@node "2" "What for devil created this util ?"

Simply: to choose startup-sequence from which computer should be started.
That was simply. Rename your original StartUp-Sequence to StartUp-Sequence-0
and reedit it like this one:

;,.StartMenu - Standard WorkBench               -       comment line

SYSPIC S:PICS/BLACK
AGAON
ASSIGN ENV: DH0:PREFS/ENV-ARCHIVE
ASSIGN ENVARC: DH0:PREFS/ENV-ARCHIVE
ASSIGN CLIPBOARDS: DH0:DEVS/CLIPBOARDS
ASSIGN LOCALE: DH0:LOCALE
ASSIGN PRINTERS: DH0:DEVS/PRINTERS
ASSIGN KEYMAPS: DH0:DEVS/KEYMAPS
CONCLIP
IPREFS
SYSPIC DH0:EXTRAS/DEMOS/AWS.SCRIPT
PATH RAM:
TCLICK 0
ASSIGN T: DH2:TRASH
ASSIGN FMS: RAM:
COPY DH0:S/def_ramDISK.INFO RAM:DISK.INFO
IF EXISTS s:user-startup
  Execute s:user-startup
EndIF
SETMAP USA-PL
PLFONTS
LOADWB
Run >NIL: <NIL: ClassPatch
ENDCLI

Now make your NEW StartUp-Sequence. Put StartMenu.exe at the top of your
StartUp-Sequence and after it put also EndCli command. New startup-sequence
should look like this:

c:startmenu.exec
endcli

If you woule like to choose many (in non registered version only 10) diffrent
startup-sequences from which should your computer be started then simply edit
them and rename them later to startup-seuqence-1, startup-seuqence-2,
startup-seuqence-3, startup-seuqence-4 ... And that's the whole philosophy of
StartMenu v.0.666. Isn't it simply ???

@endnode

@node "3" "Requirements, libraries, etc ..."

StartMenu v.0.666 requires:

- Amiga computer or compataible :-)
- OS.2.0 or grater... not tested on 1.3... :-)
- 0.5 mb chip... not tested on 256kb... :-)

That's all... See ya in hell...
@endnode
